From 24770fd35c01749ea5a470124d305e7ba7928e32 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Mykola Lysenko <nickolay.lysenko@gmail.com>
Date: Sun, 12 Jul 2026 16:02:38 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 3/5] generic/574: force real extents on btrfs for sub-page
 corruption cases

The block_size=1024 cases corrupt files as small as 1024 and 2048
bytes.  On btrfs those are stored as inline extents (default
max_inline=2048), which _fsv_scratch_corrupt_bytes cannot corrupt --
fiemap exposes no physical address for inline data -- so the test
misreported fs-verity as broken while no corruption ever reached disk.

Mount with -o max_inline=0 on btrfs so every test file gets a regular,
corruptible extent.  The option is scoped to this test rather than
common/verity because btrfs/290 deliberately corrupts inline extents
and must keep them available.

With this and the previous patch, generic/574 passes on btrfs
(previously the 1024 section failed 100% of runs) and btrfs/290 is
unaffected.

Signed-off-by: Mykola Lysenko <nickolay.lysenko@gmail.com>
---
 tests/generic/574 | 6 ++++++
 1 file changed, 6 insertions(+)

diff --git a/tests/generic/574 b/tests/generic/574
index ebe081e..6734999 100755
--- a/tests/generic/574
+++ b/tests/generic/574
@@ -25,6 +25,12 @@ _cleanup()
 . ./common/verity
 
 _require_scratch_verity
+# btrfs: files <= max_inline become inline extents, which
+# _fsv_scratch_corrupt_bytes cannot corrupt (no physical fiemap address) —
+# the block_size=1024 cases below use files that small. Force real extents.
+if [ $FSTYP == "btrfs" ]; then
+	export MOUNT_OPTIONS+=" -o max_inline=0"
+fi
 _disable_fsverity_signatures
 _require_fsverity_corruption
 
